               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl366-1">Budge, Histories ; BHO, 137. A. Scher, dans ROC 11 (1906), 403-23 ; 12 (1907), 6- 13. A. Scher, "Ecrivains", §XIV, 13- 14. A. Baumstark, "Die Biographie des Rabban bar Idta", Romische Quartalschrift 15 (1901), 115- 23 (non vidi). Etude et autres references dans Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, I, 269- 83; idem, "Bar 'Eta", 1- 16. BSO, I, 336-37 (J. Habbi).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Bar 'Edta was an important monastic founder who built a monastery in the region of Marga.  He was a disciple of Abraham the Elder, and his sister Hana Isho built a monastery dedicated to St. Febronia.</note>
